<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-87-0607 </DOCNO><TEXT>This patent describes an apparatus for the cooling of perishable materialsstored on a cart means having at least a bottom comprising: (a) a firstinsulation means extending over the bottom; (b) second flexible insulationmeans extending over the perishable material and to the bottom, the secondinsulation means having a top, sides, an inside and an outside surfacethe sides having a top and a bottom; (c) pocket means attached to thesecond insulation means and positioned on the inside of the second insulationmeans at the top of the sides the pocket means having permeable meansthrough at least a portion of the pocket means; (d) access means throughthe sides of the second insulation means to the pocket means for permittingthe insertion of refrigeration material there through and into the pocketmeans; and (e) means for closing the access means.</TEXT></DOC>